sp.p:
That word (almost) was well put in:
but to the Argument, as to Point of Government;
if unlike Christians we govern our selves,
we tacitly slide into the Inconveniency of Slaves;
and such we may suspect our selves to be, because
to sink under the weight of every single
Temptation, by which means we sully all those
excellent Privileges that adorned our Protoplast
in his Primitive State.

Is the Law of Nature a standing
Rule or no? If it be a Rule, it ought to be obeyed;
for its natural in kind to answer kind.

Then let all Suspicions suspend themselves;
so steer your Course to some other Point,
and call Agrippa from behind that Sycomore.

That's well consider'd, pray let it be so;
that without interruption we may ramble all
Scotland.

Or it may be both, for ought I know;
for it's almost impossible that one single Fish
should raise the Water to such Eruptions.

You have eminent Thoughts of Home;
but how will it happen to us here, coming so
unexpectly upon our Landlord?

Yes surely, otherwise I had lost my Expectation;
and this Day's Journey broke the
Heart of a Traveller.
